resource.title: Treatment plan for pancreatic adenocarcinoma
resource.description: Comprehensive treatment plan including Surgery, Chemotherapy, Radiotherapy

resource.conclusion: Patient shows stable status for pancreatic adenocarcinoma. Aisha Nguyen, a 54-year-old Asian female diagnosed with Stage III pancreatic adenocarcinoma, underwent pancreatectomy followed by six cycles of chemotherapy with Oxaliplatin and Fluorouracil. Subsequently, she received 15 radiation therapy sessions. The patient is currently stable with regular follow-up visits for monitoring and support.
